==English==
===Noun===
'''precipice''' ([[precipices]])

#a very steep cliff
#the brink of a dangerous situation, as in ''to stand on a precipice''

====Etymology====
First attested in [[1598]], from L. [[præcipitium]] ''a steep place'', from [[præceps]] ''steep'', from [[præ-]] ''forth'' + [[caput]] ''head''. First meaning of the noun is recorded from 1632.

====Synonyms====
*[[cliff]]

====Related terms====
*[[precipitous]]
*[[precipitously]]
*[[precipitousness]]

